    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-06-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="126"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-06-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1903</hi>
                        </date>. (Received 6.10 p.m., June 25.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>June 17, 4 p.m. Members of Congress arriving. Opposition to the ratifications of
                    the canal convention is very strong. Public opinion is that the convention will
                    not be ratified.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
